<h2> Definition </h2>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="simultaneous">@HI{{@EM{{tsutsu}}}}</a> is a conjunction indicating that two actions are performed simultaneously by the same subject.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{iroirona@FG{{@KJ{{body^verification}}:taiken}}wo@KJ{{music}}shimi@EM{{tsutsu}},@KJ{{day^book}}no@KJ{{life^lively}}ni@FG{{@KJ{{accustomed}}:na}}reteitta.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Whilst enjoying various personal experiences, I became accustomed to the Japanese way of life.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="ongoing">@HI{{@EM{{tsutsuaru}}}}</a> is an auxiliary which expresses that an action is in progress.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{orinpikku}}no@FG{{@KJ{{alms^establishment}}:shisetsu}}ga@FG{{@KJ{{exit^come}}:deki}}@EM{{tsutsuaru}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The Olympic facilities are being completed.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
@Vte{{}}@HI{{iru}} also expresses an action in progress, however, with a punctual verb the meaning is that the state has happened and persists,
not that it is in progress.

Compare the meaning of the following sentences with a punctual verb.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{dance^pedestal}}:butai}}no@FG{{@KJ{{curtain}}:maku}}ga@KJ{{open}}iteiru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The stage curtain is up.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
and

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{dance^pedestal}}:butai}}no@FG{{@KJ{{curtain}}:maku}}ga@KJ{{open}}ki@EM{{tsutsuaru}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The stage curtain is up.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@Vte{{}}@HI{{iru}} also expresses an action in progress, but with a verb of movement the meaning is that the movement has occurred and its effects persist,
not that the movement is in progress.

Compare the following sentences with a verb of movement.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{difficult^people}}:nanmin}}ha@KJ{{oneself^part^accomplished}}no@KJ{{country}}ni@KJ{{homecoming}}tteiru.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The refugees are back in their own country.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
and

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@FG{{@KJ{{difficult^people}}:nanmin}}ha@KJ{{oneself^part^accomplished}}no@KJ{{country}}ni@KJ{{homecoming}}ri@EM{{tsutsuaru}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      The refugees are returning to their own country.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

